Sec. 201.014. ELECTION. (a) The delegates at a state district
convention by majority vote shall elect a member to the state board
from among the qualified delegates. No later than the fifth day
after the day of the election, the chairman of the convention shall
certify to the state board and to the secretary of state the name and
address of the person elected.
(b) A state district convention shall conduct an election under
this section on the first Tuesday in May of each year in which the
term expires for the member of the state board representing that
district.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1462, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

